SYSTEMD AUTOSTART
=================

source: https://github.com/jceb/dex

1. Create systemd user dir


mkdir -p ~/.config/systemd/user


2. Create autostart target


touch ~/.config/systemd/user/autostart.target


3. Edit autostart with following


[Unit]
Description=Current graphical user session
Documentation=man:systemd.special(7)
RefuseManualStart=no
StopWhenUnneeded=no


4. Create service file


touch ~/.config/systemd/user/<service>.service


3. Edit service with following


[Unit]
Description=<service description>

[Service]
ExecStart=<path to the executable> [<parameters>]


4. Register the service


systemctl --user add-wants autostart.target <service>.service


5. Add following into .xinitrc


systemctl --user start autostart.target
